<HEADLINE> 4th China Int'l Folk Art Festival Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The 4th China International Folk
Art Festival opened here tonight at the Capital Indoor Stadium of
Beijing where 16 folk-art troupes from five continents performed
at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
All income from the opening ceremony and the four fund-raising
sites around the Capital Indoor Stadium will be donated to China's
flood victims, according to the festival's organizers.
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to end on August 28, the festival aims to enhance and
exchange the folk arts of many countries and deepen the friendship
among the people of various nations.
</P>
<P>
After three performances in Beijing, the artists will be
divided into two groups and continue performing in places
including east China's Jiangsu Province, Shanghai Municipality,
north China's Tianjin Municipality, and south China's Guangdong
Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
