<HEADLINE> Cyprus Condemns Arrest of Iranian Diplomats in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus has unreservedly
condemned the arrest of Iranian diplomats and a journalist by
Taliban forces last Saturday in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The condemnation as made by Cypriot Foreign Minister Ioannis
Kasoulides during a meeting Thursday with Iran's Charge
D'Affaires in Cyprus, Ali Akbar Farazi, according to an official
announcement issued here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kasoulides reassured the Iranian diplomat that Nicosia will do
everything possible to restore respect of diplomatic norms.
</P>
<P>
Farazi informed Kasoulides that Taliban's arrest of the
Iranians during the capture of the Mazari-e-Sharif town was a
violation of international diplomatic norms.
</P>
<P>
Farazi urged the Cypriot government to back others in
demanding the immediate release of the diplomats and the IRNA
correspondent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
