<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The British government Friday
appealed to British nationals to leave the Democratic Republic of
the Congo (DRC) immediately as the situation in the African
country continued worsening.
</P>
<P>
Senior aides of embattled President Laurent Kabila reportedly
admitted Thursday night that the rebels had made further advances
and taken over the distribution center at the huge Inga
hydro-electric dam in the west.
</P>
