<HEADLINE> Greek Police Confiscate 26 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 14 (xinhua) -- Greek police Friday arrested two
Albanians and found 26 kilograms of heroin in the latters'
Mercedes car.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the heroin, hidden in 51 plastic bags, was
discovered in the double-bottom tank of the car driven by the
Albanians, who entered the northeastern Greek Kipi border crossing
from neighboring Turkey, the semi-official Athens News Agency
(ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the two Albanians were believed to belong to
an organized heroin gang smuggling large quantities of narcotics
from Turkey to the countries of western Europe. 
