<HEADLINE> Angolan Police Detained Three for Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Police have detained three
persons for illegal cocaine trafficking, the Angolan National
Police Headquarters said in a communique Friday.
</P>
<P>
Two Angolans came to Luanda Airport to collect their "cargo"
from Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, but police found about 30 cocaine
among canned fruit and packed coffee.
</P>
<P>
The two, detained on the spot, are believed to be members of a
drug trafficking group, and the cocaine was to be sold in Angola
and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Another man involved in the case has also been detained by
police.
</P>
<P>
Police said that more drug is feared to be smuggled into the
country from Brazil, another Portuguese-speaking country by the
other side of Atlantic.  
</P>
