<HEADLINE> Bonn Hails Rugova's Move to Resume Kosovo Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Germany Friday welcomed a peace
move made by Kosovo Albanian leader Ibrahim Rugova to resume the
political dialogue in Yugoslavia's troubled province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Friday in Bonn, German Foreign Minister
Klaus Kinkel described Rugova's decision to form a five-member
negotiating team as "an important first step on the difficult path
to a political solution to the Kosovo conflict."
</P>
<P>
Kinkel also urged the Yugoslav government to intensively
participate in the peace talks which have been suspended since
June, adding that "a serious dialogue was at least a glimmer of
hope for the political solution."
</P>
<P>
The negotiating team named by Rugova Friday, however, failed to
include members from the Kosovo Liberation Army, the rebel group
which has been fighting Serbian security forces for Kosovo's
independence for the past six months.
</P>
<P>
"It must remain the goal of all Kosovo Albanian politicians to
build an all-party negotiating platform accepted by all segments
of the Kosovo Albanian population," Kinkel said. 
</P>
