<HEADLINE> French Troops to Join Military Exercise in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- French troops will join a
15-nation military exercise in Albania from August 17 to 22, said
the French Defense Ministry Friday.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, called "Cooperative Assembly 98," will be held
under the southern command of NATO allied forces.
</P>
<P>
Being "an initiative of partnership for peace," the exercise
will include both a purely operational exercise and one with civil
and military characteristics, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
It is aimed at training the commanding staff of NATO's southern
wing and the units of the countries participating in it in a
scenario of common action in a zone of insecurity, said the
ministry.
</P>
<P>
The exercise will also stress the inter-dependence of the
ground force, air force and navy, it said.
</P>
<P>
The NATO forces will also hold a joint exercise of humanitarian
operation with Albanian troops.
</P>
<P>
France will send two Jaguar combat aircraft and two C 135 oil
supply planes to join the exercise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
