Islamic extremists against the United States and its citizens and
because of the possibility that the U.S. embassy in Tirana...
could be among the targets of a terrorist attack."
</P>
<P>
The travel warning follows an announcement late Thursday that
the embassy in Tirana was temporarily suspending normal
operations.
</P>
<P>
About 5,000 were wounded and more than 250 were killed in the
U.S. embassy bombings in Kenya and Tanzania. Eleven American
citizens were dead. 
