<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will clear the way for its
full participation in the ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA) plan
scheduled for 2006 as it has committed, the Vietnam News Agency
Saturday quoted a government official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has pledged to apply tariffs of up to five percent on
at least 85 percent of its goods sold in regional markets by 2006,
said deputy minister for foreign affairs, Nguyen Tam Chien.
</P>
<P>
