countries of the ASEAN affirmed their commitments to obtain
regional trade liberation despite adverse impacts caused by the
current financial turmoil on their economies.
</P>
<P>
According to the deputy foreign minister, an agreement to
establish an ASEAN investment area would be likely to be signed in
the near future. Other regional accords, including an agreement
on multi-lateral communications, the second phase of an ASEAN
agreement on free services and other sub-regional cooperation
agreements, are expected to be reached soon.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's admission to ASEAN in 1995 marked the integration of
the Vietnamese economy into the regional and world economy, Chien
affirmed. 
