<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Animal Hearts to be Transplanted into Human Bodies (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- "Man with the heart of a beast"
might be used literarily to describe a man with a heart
transplanted from a transgenic pig in the next century when
scientists succeed in using transgenic animal organs for human
patients.
</P>
<P>
Scientists predict that xenotransplantation, the
transplantation of transgenic organs from one species to another,
might be used to help human patients who need organ transplants,
within 15 to 20 years.
</P>
<P>
"The incentive for xenotransplantation study lies in the
shortage of human organ donors," said Doctor Hester Kuipers from
the Novartis Company of Imutran Ltd., Cambridge, UK, who is here
attending the 18th International Congress on Genetics. She said
that the number of patients waiting for organ transplants is six
times that of the number of organ donors in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Kuipers and other scientists at Novartis, which is a
world-leader in xenotransplantation studies, are trying to
grow transgenic pig organs that will not cause hyperacute
rejection in human bodies.
</P>
<P>
She said the transgenic pigs were produced by micro-injecting a
complementary DNA (cDNA) construct for the human decaying accelerating
factor (hDAF), a kind of protein, into the fertilized eggs of
pigs. New-born pigs in the breeding program were first screened for
the presence of the transgene by genetic methods.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980815.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Animal Organs to be Transplanted Into Human Bodies (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Experiments have shown that organs from hDAF transgenic pigs
were not hyperacutely rejected, she said, adding that they have
transplanted hearts from transgenic pigs to cynomolgus monkeys,
and one of the monkeys survived for 99 days after the operation.
</P>
<P>
The reason for using pigs for xenotransplantation is that the
heart, kidney and other organs of transgenic pig are more similar
to human organs in shape and size than other species.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Kuipers said that her company has been involved in
xenotransplantation study for ten years, and is making rapid
developments. But the technique will not be mature enough to be
used for humans until the early 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chinese scientists have also started xenotransplantation
research, and they will try to transplant transgenic pig hearts into
monkeys by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Experimentation on the transplantation of tissues and cells from
transgenic animals have also demonstrated some gratifying results.
</P>
<P>
However, scientists are conducting experiments to find if
transgenic organs will bring viruses from the animals into human bodies
or cause other side-effects. Eventually, social scientists may
consider a new definition for men with transgenic animal organs.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980815.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Administrative Secretary Returns from Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Anson Chan, administrative
secretary of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR),
Saturday expressed the hope that the Asian economies will pick up
again very soon.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on her early estimation that the economic
recession might last for 2-3 years at the meet-the-media session
upon her return to Hong Kong from Singapore Saturday afternoon,
Chan said that it's very difficult for anybody "to estimate how
long the difficulties we are currently facing on the economic
front will last."
</P>
<P>
Of course, "we all hope that the Asian economies will pick up
again very very soon but to a large extent, as I have pointed out,
it depends on the Japanese leadership and vision."
</P>
<P>
"It depends on Japan taking measures to deal with the financial
reforms and to be back to normal situation, and to take measures
to stabilize the Japanese yen and resume consumers' confidence,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
"In the wake of that", she said: "I am sure we will see
economies in this region improving."
</P>
<P>
Talking about the measures that Financial Secretary Donald
Tsang has taken to draw upon the resources of the exchange fund to
counterattack speculators in the stock and futures markets, Chan
stressed that the government will not deviate its consistent
non-interference policy.
</P>
<P>
However, she said: "we can not tolerate any creation of
distortion in foreign exchange market to affect our economic
system.
</P>
<P>
"The special action that we have adopted aims at directing
specifically against the speculative activities", she added.
</P>
</TEXT>
