<HEADLINE> Kunming Export Commodities Trade Fair Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Kunming Export
Commodities Trade Fair closed today in this capital of southwest
China's Yunnan Province with a total trade volume reaching 1.81
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shao Qiwei, deputy director of the organizing committee of the
trade fair and vice-governor of Yunnan Province, said the Kunming
fair has become a window and bridge linking southwest China and
the rest of the world, and that its total trade volume increased
by 16.8 percent from the last fair.
</P>
<P>
Despite the impact of the financial crisis in Southeast Asia,
this year's trade fair still scored remarkable achievements and
drew increasing participation from more than 1,000 overseas
business people from 14 countries and regions, said Shao.
</P>
<P>
Provinces, municipality and autonomous regions in southwest
China have signed 61 contracts with present overseas enterprises,
with a total contractual investment of 788 million
U.S. dollars. Ten large contracts, each with an investment
exceeding 30 million U.S. dollars, are for transportation,
industry, and tourism.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, the Kunming Export Commodities Trade Fair is a
regional fair that mainly targets Southeast Asia. The fair has
been held each year since 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
