<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-six ethnic Albanians
were charged on Friday with terrorism-related crimes by a local
procuratorate in Yugoslavia's troubled province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The move came as the ethnic Albanian leadership agreed on
resumed talks with Belgrade over the crisis which has existed in
Kosovo since February.
</P>
<P>
The Pech Prefectural Procuratorate had asked the local court to
start relevant investigations into the accusations, the Yugoslav
