<P>
Ibranhim Rugova, the main Kosovo ethnic Albanian leader, named
a five-person delegation, on Friday, to restart suspended peace
talks with Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Ethnic Albanians, seeking independence from Yugoslavia and
integration into neighboring Albania, boycotted the talks in
March, and they were suspended in June.
</P>
<P>
Tension has run high in Kosovo, where ethnic Albanian outnumber
Serbs nine to one, since February when ethnic Albanians clashed
with Serb police and mounted numerous attacks on police
installations. 
