<HEADLINE> Concert Ends in Harbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A ten-day concert held in Harbin,
capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, ended today.
</P>
<P>
The 24th Harbin Summer Concert was jointly sponsored by the
Ministry of Culture and the Harbin city government. More than 60
nationwide troupes and over 4,000 actors and actresses took part
in the concert.
</P>
<P>
Artists from U.S and Iceland also presented wonderful
performances at the concert. More than one million Harbin
residents watched the performances.
</P>
<P>
The concert was held first in 1961. It has been developed into
a high-level musical event which combines classic music
performances with people's cultural activities. 
