<HEADLINE> PLA, Armed Police Make Donations to Flood-Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- China's People's Liberation Army
(PLA) and the armed police forces have donated more than 20
million yuan worth of relief goods to flood victims along the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The donations came from hundreds of generals on the
flood-fighting frontiers, thousands of retired PLA officers across
the country, and millions of ordinary soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Local governments and ordinary citizens are also making their
contributions to the ongoing flood relief work. In southwest
China's Sichuan Province, ordinary people and local organizations
have donated more than 36 million yuan worth of goods to the flood
victims.
</P>
<P>
On the morning of August 11, Wang Shuang, a sixth-grade primary
school student, sent 100 yuan RMB to the Disaster Relief Office of
the provincial Department of Civil Affairs, the first donation
received by the office since the department called on everyone to
make donations to the flood victims on August 10.
</P>
<P>
On August 12, the provincial government sent 220 tons of pork
and some 500,000 yuan worth of medicines to the flood-ravaged
provinces as Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi and Anhui.
</P>
<P>
"Although Sichuan is also a victim of the rampant floods,
provinces on the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River
need the medicines more," said Xie Shijie, secretary of the
Sichuan Provincial Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC).
</P>
<P>
In an another development, officials and staff of the organs
under the General Office of the CPC Central Committee have so far
donated a total of 2.07 million yuan to the flood-stricken areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
