<HEADLINE> State Council Circular Calls for Epidemic Disease Prevention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- An urgent circular from the
State Council, China's highest governing body, calls for diligence
in the effort to prevent epidemic disease both during this season
of raging floods and after the waters subside.
</P>
<P>
So far, social and economic order has remained stable in the
flood-besieged areas. However, the experience of history shows
that large outbreaks of epidemic disease may easily occur
following natural disasters, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
Local governments and health care departments should take heed
to strengthen their leadership over disaster relief and disease
prevention efforts, the circular says, adding that the Ministry of
Health should send groups of experts and national medical teams to
the flooded areas, and leaders should head for the front line.
</P>
<P>
Health departments should adhere to the regulation calling for
close supervision of epidemic disease potential, and timely
reporting during times of emergency, it says.
</P>
<P>
The masses should be mobilized to maintain a clean environment
and try their best to remove any conditions that could possibly
trigger an outbreak of epidemic disease. Efforts should also be
exerted to protect water resources and sterilize water for
drinking, the circular adds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
