<HEADLINE> Ningxia Builds Its First Modern Meeting Hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN August 15 (Xinhua) -- The first modern,
multi-functional and comprehensive meeting hall ever constructed
in Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region, was completed today.
</P>
<P>
Covering an area of 18,000 square meters, the hall was built at
a cost of over 66 million yuan (about 8.2 million U.S.
dollars). A variety of activities such as meetings, trade fairs,
cultural performances, and movie screening can be held in the
building's first-class facilities.
</P>
<P>
Celebration activities for the fortieth anniversary of
the autonomous region's founding will be held
in the newly built meeting hall in September. 
