<HEADLINE> Flood-Fighting Tops Government Agenda: Jiang Zemin (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Flood-fighting is now at the top
of the agenda of local governments along the Yangtze River and all
efforts should be made to ensure the safety of the embankments of
the river, Chinese President Jiang Zemin stressed in flood-ravaged
central China's province of Hubei in a Friday speech, which was
made public today.
</P>
<P>
Top priority should be given to safeguarding the lives of the
people during this effort, Jiang said during an inspection of
Hubei Province Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang inspected a number of embankment sections in danger along
the Yangtze, conveyed his concern to local residents and soldiers,
and listened to briefings from local leaders.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, pointed out that
"flood-fighting along the Yangtze River area has reached a crucial
moment when problems may easily appear and carelessness is liable
to cause huge losses".
</P>
<P>
All of the country's forces should make continued and concerted
efforts to support civilians and soldiers who are on the
flood-fighting front lines until a final victory is achieved, he
urged.
</P>
<P>
He said that outstanding successes have already been achieved
in fighting the raging floods in Fujian, Guangxi, Hunan, Hubei,
Jiangxi, Anhui, Jiangsu, Heilongjiang, Jilin, and Inner Mongolia
since mid-June.
</P>
<P>
During the unprecedented struggle against the Yangtze floods, a
large number of civilians and soldiers have scored a vital victory
by defending the river dikes for more than 40 days and
withstanding five flood crests, he added.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the victory to the strong leadership of the
Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party, the concerted
efforts by the millions of people and soldiers, the all-out
support by the whole nation, the growing base of both materials
and technology, and the water control system built up in recent
decades.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the army and armed police have won the acclaim of
the people by going all out to join in the flood-fighting work.
So far, 130,000 soldiers equipped with 5,800 vehicles and 860
boats have been deployed along the middle and lower reaches of the
Yangtze River.
</P>
</TEXT>
