<HEADLINE> Ye Takes on Susanti in Singapore Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Ye Zhaoying beat Gong Zhichao
in an all-Chinese women's singles semifinal at the Singapore Open
badminton tournament here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ye, who faced little challenge in her 11-8, 11-2 victory over
Gong, will vie for the title against Indonesian Susi Susanti.
</P>
<P>
Susanti overcame early setbacks to nip Denmark's Camilla
Martin 3-11, 11-6, 11-2.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Peter-Gade Christensen of Denmark erased a game-two
slump against Malaysian Yong Hock Kin to enter the men's singles
final.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old world champion, who won 17-15, 5-15, 15-9,
will meet Indonesia's eighth-seeded H. Hendrawan for the singles
title on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian on Saturday outclassed China's All-England
champion and second seed Sun Jun 15-10, 15-6 in the other
semi-final.
</P>
<P>
The men's singles winner will pocket 11,050 U.S. dollars while
the women's champion takes home 8,500 dollars. 
</P>
