<HEADLINE> Shanghai Company Merges with Prestigious Design Institutes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Tunnel Engineering
Holding Ltd (STE), China's first listed construction company, has
merged with two prestigious design institutes as part of the
effort to improve its technological development capacity.
</P>
<P>
The two institutes were formerly under the Shanghai Urban
Construction Group Corp. (SUC), China's largest urban construction
enterprise.
</P>
<P>
SUC President Gao Kang said yesterday that intellectual
property rights represent an extremely important asset which will
protect the company's development potential. He said the merger
with the two institutes is an asset investment which will be
conducive to strengthening cooperation between the two urban
construction giants in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The two institutes -- the Shanghai Tunnel Engineering and Rail
Communications Design Institute and the Shanghai Urban Planning
Institute -- are renowned for the construction of metropolitan
subways and expressways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
