<HEADLINE> Flood-Fighting Tops Government Agenda: Jiang Zemin (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"At present, the situation remains tough along the Yangtze
River," Jiang said, noting that new flood crests may occur as
rainfall is expected on the upper reaches of the river.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we should redouble our efforts and do a better job
in mobilizing, organizing the flood-fighting work," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang demanded that leaders at all levels place great
importance on the flood-fighting effort and give it top priority,
and told them they are all responsible for the effort.
</P>
<P>
Each locality and concerned department and forces from
everywhere should firmly obey orders from the State Flood Control
and Drought Relief Headquarters, he said.
</P>
<P>
The People's Liberation Army should play the role of shock
troops, overcoming fatigue and sharpening vigilance to make new
contributions, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also called for timely efforts to evacuate the people in
dangerous places and ensure they are provided with adequate food,
boiled water, housing, and access to medical service, adding that
attention must be paid to epidemic prevention and public security.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary to step up efforts in maintaining normal
public order and crack down sternly on various kinds of crimes,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, governments at various levels should work out plans
to help local people restore production and rebuild their homes,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader noted that water control efforts are very
important for maintaining social order and invigorating the
nation. Floods, a hidden trouble threatening the lives, property
and safety of the people, should arouse high concern from the
whole Party.
</P>
<P>
The central authorities, as well as local governments, have
always attached great importance to strengthening the country's
water-control ability, and have adopted a series of measures to
increase investment in this regard, he said.
</P>
<P>
"However, the water-control ability of our country is still not
very strong, and this requires further effective measures," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that immediately after the present flooding
season, it is necessary that the government work out and implement
efficient measures to build water-control facilities and raise the
capacity for flood prevention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
