<HEADLINE> Zanzibar President Expresses Sympathy to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Zanzibar President Salmin
Amour has sent a message to Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
expressing his sympathy with China and its people who have
suffered a great deal from the rampant floods.
</P>
<P>
In a message to Chinese President Jiang Zemin on Friday, Amour
said, "I take this opportunity on behalf of the government and on
my own behalf to send our heartfelt condolences to the bereaved
families and their relatives and console those who continue to
suffer from the floods."
</P>
<P>
"We commend the people of the People's Republic of China and
the Chinese army for their untiring efforts in containing the
situation," he said in the message, made available here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"During this time of grief, the government and the people of
Zanzibar and myself would like to express again our sentiments of
profound sorrow and grief," it went on.
</P>
<P>
"I also wish the people of the People's Republic of China
every prosperity, progress, success and continued strong
relations between the two countries and peoples," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar, part of the United Republic of Tanzania, is
consisted of the twin islands of Unguja, Pemba and a number of
smaller islands in the Indian Ocean off the coast of the
mainland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
