<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Denies Abduction of Indian Embassy Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the Pakistani
Foreign Office Saturday denied India's accusation that its
intelligence agency has abducted one of India's embassy staff.
</P>
<P>
"There is no truth in it," the spokesman categorically stated
in his weekly briefing here.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Foreign Ministry issued a statement on Friday saying
a staff member from its high commission in Islamabad and his
three-year-old son were kidnapped by four "Pakistani intelligence
operatives" on August 10.
</P>
<P>
The statement said India had lodged a "strong protest" against
the incident and asked Pakistan to immediately investigate it.
</P>
