<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Plans to Receive Congo (K) Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees are taking urgent measures to prepare
for the influx of refugees from the Democratic Republic of Congo
(DRC) where rebels are fighting against the government.
</P>
<P>
Lennart Korsalainen, the acting representative of the UNHCR
office in Tanzania, said here Saturday that the agency plans to
open a new reception center in case the refugees from DRC
drastically increase.
</P>
<P>
The center, built last year in the Kibondo District, in west
Tanzania's Kigoma Region, has not received any refugees. The
center was originally planned for refugees from Burundi or other
countries, Korsalainen told Xinhua in a telephone interview.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, whether or not to settle down the refugees
in the center is up to the government of Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Korsalainen said the refugees fleeing the DRC into Tanzania
are increasing day by day, and reached 159 on Thursday. But these
days the new arrivals have been "very few".
</P>
<P>
The refugees, fleeing by boats across the Lake Tanganyika on
the border between DRC and Tanzania, are currently sheltered at a
reception in the Kigoma town on the shore of the lake.
</P>
<P>
The UNHCR office in Tanzania has requested a contingency
budget from its headquarters in Geneva for expanding food and
other services, he said, adding the exact amount of fund needed
will depend on the scale of refugee influx. 
</P>
</TEXT>
