<HEADLINE> 8 More Die in Landslide in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 15 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people died
Thursday in landslides triggered by monsoon rains in two districts
of Nepal, the media here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Five members of a family including four children in Nuwakot
district, 50 kilometers northwest of Kathmandu, died when their
house collapsed in landslide, the Kantipur Daily said.
</P>
<P>
At least three others of a family died in landslide in Baglung
district, western Nepal, Radio Nepal said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At least 113 people had died in floods and landslides by August
5 across the country, the Home Ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
