</P>
<P>
-- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat is due in Cairo Monday to
discuss with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak the latest
developments in the Mideast peace process and efforts to persuade
the U.S. to publicize its proposal on Israeli troop pullback.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. proposal calls on Israel to hand over to the
Palestinians 13 percent more of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
