</P>
<P>
-- Egypt and a number of the Non-Aligned Movement countries are
maintaining contacts to set the scene for the upcoming summit on
August 30 in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, an Egyptian working paper dealing with terrorism
will be discussed.
</P>
<P>
The Mideast peace process will also be the focus of discussion
at the upcoming summit.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Mail:
</P>
<P>
-- Officials from the World Bank, Arab Development Fund and
Kuwaiti Development Fund are undertaking negotiations on the final
formula of financing Egypt's Toshka project through a 350 million
U.S. dollars soft loan.
</P>
<P>
The formula will be submitted respectively to the boards of
chairmen of the three organizations for approval in September.
</P>
<P>
The Toshka project is designed to divert water from the Nile
River to irrigate the western desert area. 
