<HEADLINE> Rockers Beat Sting in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Cleveland Rockers kept
their Eastern Conference lead by beating the Charlotte Sting
85-72 in a WNBA game in Charlotte on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Merlakia Jones netted 12 of her 14 points in the last five
minutes for Cleveland, which won its first game in four actions
in Charlotte. Suzie McConnell Serio added a career-high 18 points
and seven assists.
</P>
<P>
Cleveland, which has two games left in the regular season,
also got 16 points from Isabelle Fijalkowski, and 15 from Eva N
emcova and 10 from Rushia Brown.
</P>
<P>
Charlotte, which has one game left, lost its fourth
consecutive game while the Sting was beaten for the ninth time in
13 games.
</P>
<P>
Andrea Stinson scored 20 points for Charlotte, and Tracy Reid
added 19.
</P>
<P>
In the other two games tonight, the Phoenix Mercury beat the
Detroit Shock 84-59 and the Los Angeles Sparks defeated Utah
Starzz 87-67. 
</P>
</TEXT>
