<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thompson Wins 20th National Swimming Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Jenny Thompson claimed her
20th national title Friday night, winning the 100-meter butterfly
in the U.S. Swimming Championships in Fresno, California on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Thompson becomes the 16th swimmer to win 20 national
titles.
</P>
<P>
Thompson who won the 100 freestyle earlier this week and will
swim the 50 freestyle on Saturday, said "I feel privileged to be
in that category but I don't think I will swim long enough to get
to the top of that list."
</P>
<P>
Tracy Caulkins won 48 titles to rank first.
</P>
<P>
Lenny Krayzelburg captured his second title, taking the men's
100 backstroke in 54.64 after his victory in the 200 backstroke
earlier in the week.
</P>
<P>
Barbara Bedford took the women's 100 backstroke title in
1:01.11, beating 1996 Olympic gold medalist Beth Botsford and Lea
Maurer, who finished second. Botsford was fourth.
</P>
<P>
Cristina Teuscher, who was second in both the 400 individual
medley and the 200 freestyle on Thursday, won the 400 freestyle
in 4:10.80, just eight-hundredths of second faster than
15-year-old Melissa Deary.
</P>
<P>
Rick Vendt touched home first in the men's 400 freestyle in
3:51.23, Kristy Kowal won the women's 100 breaststroke in a meet
record time of 1:08.71 while Kurt Grote took the men's 100
breaststroke title in 1:01.60 and Brock Newman won the men's 100
butterfly in 53.24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
