<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fourth Flood Peak Passes Major Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The fourth flood crest of the
Nenjiang River is passing Qiqihar, causing no losses to this city
of one million people in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
By 10:00 today, the water level at the city stood at 149.15
meters, 15 centimeters lower than yesterday's mark, indicating the
water level is slowly dropping at the Qiqihar section.
</P>
<P>
However, the water at different sections of the river still
remain at record-high levels, indicating the flood situation is
still severe, experts said.
</P>
<P>
In its anti-flood fight over the past 50 days, the city,
located to the northwest of Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang
Province, has evacuated over 300,000 residents to safe locations
and ensured the safety of the nearby cities, towns and large
reservoirs. No death has been reported so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
