<HEADLINE> Shanghai Improving Power Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The municipality of Shanghai is
joining 39 cities in planning a massive improvement program for
its power network by spending 4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The project involves automating the network with advanced
technology and equipment with a power development strategy of
turning away from building power plants to improving power-supply
networks.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai will replace all outdated transmission and transformer
facilities that were installed before 1949 with more powerful
equipment and set up more equipment in downtown and other urban
areas.
</P>
<P>
By year 2000, the city's power network will be able to provide
51.5 billion kwh of electricity, or 7.4 billion kwh more than that
of 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
