<HEADLINE> 100 Bangladeshi Fishermen Missing in Bay of Bengal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- At least 100 Bangladeshi fishermen
are missing in the Bay of Bengal after 21 fishing trawlers and
boats capsized in high waves due to downpour and storm during the
past four days, media reports here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 fishermen aboard the capsized trawlers and boats
managed to swim ashore and were admitted to local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday morning, 23 fishermen were reportedly missing after
two fishing boats capsized in the Bay of Bengal.
</P>
<P>
The two fishing boats, with 47 fishermen aboard, sank near
Sonachhora in Banshkhali coastal area, southeastern Chittagong
district, following heavy rain that turned the sea rough.
Twenty-four of them were rescued by nearby fishing boats.
</P>
<P>
The local administration and rescuers from Chittagong Port were
continuing the search for the missing fishermen, the reports said.
 
