<HEADLINE> Vietnam Accelerates Bilateral Cooperation with Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is giving "strategic
priority" to the traditional friendship and comprehensive
cooperation with Russia, on the basis of the two countries'
stability and mutual long-term interest, Vietnam's President Tran
Duc Luong told Itar-Tass news agency Friday.
</P>
<P>
Luong, who will visit Russia later this month, said his visit
was to "discuss with President Boris Yeltsin and other Russian
leaders the major measures and developing orientations to help
boost the comprehensive cooperation between Vietnam and Russia."
</P>
<P>
He added that both countries' efforts had led to new
development in the all-round cooperation in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Luong said Vietnam and Russia "have enough conditions and
capacity" to continue to develop cooperation, particularly in the
petrol and chemical industries, electric energy, mechanical
engineering and tropical farm products processing.
</P>
<P>
The annual trade turnover between Vietnam and Russia has
reached about 300 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are seeking measures to overcome difficulties
in business mechanisms, especially in payment forms, to enhance
trade and to raise annual turnover to 500 million dollars. 
</P>
