<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, August 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The General Motors strikes caused the worst
back-to-back declines in the U.S. industrial production in July in
nearly eight years, the Federal Reserve reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The nearly two-month-long GM strikes caused production at
factories, mines and utilities to fall 0.6 percent last month, the
second consecutive decline, according to the report.
(US-Industrial Production-July)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The British government has gained a massive windfall
from the introduction of a new self-assessment tax payment scheme,
but the sharp rise in tax receipts is considered to have
contributed to the slowdown in the UK economy.
</P>
<P>
Payments in the first two months of this year alone had risen
by 7.5 billion pounds (about 12 billion U.S. dollars), a massive
rise equivalent to raising the tax rate by over 3 percent. This
has prompted allegations that the government has implemented a
"secret" tax increase. (UK-Economy-Taxation)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea has rejected a demand by the United States
to lower its tariff of 8 percent on imported cars.
</P>
<P>
South Korea will not negotiate the tariff rate on auto imports,
said Chung Eui-yong, deputy minister of state for trade on
Friday. (SKorea-US-Tariff)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- Brazilian state-owned oil company Petrobras
had a total income of 499 million reals (434 million U.S. dollars)
in the first six months of this year, 98 percent more than in the
same period in 1997. (Brazil-Oil Income)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
VARNA -- A United States-Greece consortium signed here Friday a
stock purchase agreement to formally become the majority
shareholder in the Bulgarian Post Bank (BPB).
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the American Life Insurance Co. (ALICO)
and the Consolidated Eurofinance Holdings (CEH) will each acquire
half of the 78.23 percent of BPB's shares.
(Bulgaria-Bank-Shares-Sale) 
</P>
