<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 15 (Xinhua) -- International tenders for the
construction of the proposed Colombo-Katunayake airport express
highway will be called within the next two months, according to
Transport and Highway Ministry sources here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 31-kilometer expressway is expected to be carried out on a
turn-key basis, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The expressway is estimated to cost about 15 billion rupees
(228 million U.S. dollars) which will be provided by the Japanese
aid group, Japanese International Cooperation Agency.
</P>
<P>
The Colombo-Katunayake expressway, initially proposed in the
early 1990s, has been delayed due to alleged human rights
violations due to the relocation of thousands of residents along
the route and a number of environmental concerns, according to the
sources. 
</P>
