<HEADLINE> German Shooting Coach to Train Bangladeshi Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 15 (Xinhua) -- A German shooting coach will come
here Sunday to help train the Bangladeshi team which will take
part in the 16th Commonwealth Games, scheduled to be held in
Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia on September 11-21 this year, a press relea
se said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Uber Richter, a reputed shooting coach, will
immediately start training the Bangladeshi team whose preparation
has been hampered by continuous flood in the country for the past
one and a half months.
</P>
<P>
Since the 50-meter range in Dhaka has gone under water, the
training of the shooting team has been seriously affected,
according to the National Shooting Federation.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi shooting team will take part in eight events
out of which five will take place at the 50-meter range.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh, participating in the Games for the 6th occasion,
will send an 84-member team to compete in six disciplines --
athletics, aquatics (swimming), shooting, cricket, hockey (men)
and weightlifting -- out of the Games' 15 events of sports.
</P>
<P>
Other events of the Games are badminton, boxing, cycling,
gymnastics, lawn tennis, netball, rugby, squash and ten-pin
bowling.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh contingent, besides 10 officials, is expected
to include nine participants in athletics, five in swimming, 17
in shooting, six in weightlifting, 20 in hockey and 17 in cricket.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the Games will be held in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh won its first Commonwealth gold in shooting in the
14th Games in New Zealand in January 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
