<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Says No Outside Interference Tolerated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar adheres to the U.N.
Charter and never interfere in the internal affairs of others and
will never tolerate any outside interference, Saturday's official
paper the New Light of Myanmar quoted Myanmar leader as saying.
</P>
<P>
At a graduation ceremony of the cadets here Friday, General
Maung Aye, deputy commander-in-chief of Defense Services, said
that some big Western countries are practicing hegemony on small
nations from all corners after the power-balance system between
the East Bloc and the West Bloc ended.
</P>
<P>
As the army believes that the strength of the nation lies
within, the internal problems will be solved among the nation's
people and will never accept any outside interference, added the
general.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on transferring over the state power, Maung Aye
stressed that the army has no desire to always take charge of all
the state responsibilities and that it will abide by the
principles of the new state constitution that will emerge in the
future. 
</P>
