<HEADLINE> Second Dike Breach Near Largest oilfield </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Daqing, August 15 (Xinhua) -- Another dike section of the
flooded Nenjiang River near China's largest oilfield of Daqing
breached in the small hours this morning. Most of the local
residents are said to have been evacuated to safe places, with no
casualties reported so far.
</P>
<P>
The breach, occurred on the Pangtoupao section in Zhaoyuan
County of northeast China's Heilongjiang province, is said to pose
threat to two oilfields of Daqing and a nearby railway. The size
of the breach and the relief situation are not yet clear.
</P>
<P>
This is the second dike breach near Daqing City. The flood
caused by the first breach recorded at 06:00 am yesterday, was
approaching the secondary dike protecting Daqing City at 8:00 am
today. 
</P>
