<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian Aeronautics
Company (Embraer) earned 47.2 million reals (43 million U.S
dollars) in the first half of 1998, the newspaper Jornal de
Brazil reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The company obtained a gross income of 651.5 million reals (592
million dollars) and accumulated a growth of 126.8 percent
compared to the same period last year, when it registered a gross
income of 287.2 million reals (261 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the company, 89 percent of the gross income of
this year came from the export of aircraft, especially regional
civilian aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Embraer is a major construction company in the South American
aeronautics sector. It was founded in 1969, with its production
facilities based in Sao Jose Dos Campos, 80 kilometers from Sao
Paulo.
</P>
<P>
Embraer has sold more than 5,000 civilian and military aircraft
since its foundation, most of them for export. The company was
privatized in 1994. 
