<HEADLINE> U.S.-Greece Group Buys Majority Shares of Bulgaria's Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VARNA, Bulgaria, August 14 (Xinhua) -- A United States-Greece
consortium signed here Friday a stock purchase agreement to
formally become the majority shareholder in the Bulgarian Post
Bank (BPB).
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the American Life Insurance Co. (ALICO)
and the Consolidated Eurofinance Holdings (CEH) will each acquire
half of the 78.23 percent of BPB's shares.
</P>
<P>
The consortium pledges in the agreement to invest 20 million
U.S. dollars to increase the BPB's capital during the first year
of management.
</P>
<P>
The new owners also agreed not to sell any of their shares in
the bank for at least seven years.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian government will get 10 percent of the after-tax
profit of the consortium's BPB shares.
</P>
<P>
The Bulgarian Post Bank operates through 30 district branches,
81 offices, and 2,792 desks in shared premises. Last year it
reported an after-tax profit of 14,300 million leva (about eight
million U.S. dollars). 
