<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Customs Inspectors Intercept Drugs in Varna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian customs inspectors
seized 668.9 kilograms cocaine in the Black Sea harbor city Varna
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest amount of drug seized in Europe this year,
the Director General of the Customs Office, Plamen Minev, said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The customs inspectors found the seal of a container broken
during a routine check. They searched carefully and discovered
drug hidden inside the container.
</P>
<P>
The haul was put under close surveillance and the Bulgarian
authorities did not reveal its source and destination.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian customs have seized a total of 100 kilograms of drugs
in 31 trafficking cases in the first seven months of this year,
including 17 cases involving 94 kilograms of heroin and six cases
involving 1.4 kilograms cocaine.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria, an important link between Europe and Asia, has become
a transfer station for smuggling drugs from Asia and Latin America
to central and western Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
