<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prices of 900 Medicines Frozen in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Commerce Commission of
the Legislative Assembly and representatives of laboratories and
distributors have agreed to freeze the prices of the 900
pharmaceutical products, a report from the Commission of Free
Competence and Consumer Affairs of Panama said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A reduction in the price of medicines most in demand in
Panama could start in a period of 15 to 30 days.
</P>
<P>
After the repeal of price controls two years ago, 961 medicines
increased their price by 30 percent, 13 increased 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest studies, the medicines increase their
price 63 percent over their production cost, since the
distributors apply a 30 percent rate of profit, and the drug
stores 33 percent.
</P>
<P>
The same source said that legislators, laboratories and
distributors are drafting a list of 350 generic names of
medicines, of which the prices will be lowered in 15 days.
</P>
<P>
The freeze has been applied to prevent an increase in prices
before the reductions come into effect, said Assemblywoman Balbina
Barrera, president of the legislative commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
