<HEADLINE> Southern China's Growing Number Of Mobile Phone Customers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 15 (Xinhua) -- The number of mobile phone
customers in Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong Province,
has been growing by 10,000 or so monthly since 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the city now has more than 700,000
mobile phone customers, which means that there is one mobile
phone for every 7 adults.
</P>
<P>
Mobile phone services here have been trying to provide new
services to meet to needs of people with a range of incomes.
</P>
<P>
Spending by Guangzhou's residents on telecommunications in the
first half of this year was up 29 percent from the same period
last year. 
</P>
