<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Hopes to Play in England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian super star Ronaldo
said that he hope to play for the Manchester United or Arsenal in
England some day.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports on Friday, Ronaldo, who had his
World Cup champion dream ruined in France last month, admitted
that his ambition was to play in the Premiership -- either at Old
Trafford or Highbury.
</P>
<P>
"I am looking forward to going back to Italy -- I like it
there very much," he said from his home in Rio de Janeiro. "But
one day, I want to play in England, either for Manchester United
or Arsenal."
</P>
<P>
"I have been to England only once, but I follow the English
championship and know everything about it. It has improved a
lot."
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo will fly to Europe with his actress girlfriend Susana
Werner next week. He admitted that he had "not yet been asked"
by any clubs to play in the Premiership. 
</P>
