<HEADLINE> Albright Meets Japan's Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright on Friday pressed Japan to act quickly to revitalize its
economy while Japan's foreign minister promised to do what was
needed for the recovery.
</P>
<P>
"I will stress again today that a strong Japanese economy is
important not only for Japan but for the rest of the world, and
that we look to the new government of Prime Minister (Kaizo)
Obuchi for quick and decisive action," Albright told reporters
before talks with Japanese Foreign Minister Masahiko Komura.
</P>
