Komura said the Obuchi cabinet had put first priority on
economy and was determined to make every possible effort for the
economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
"The Obuchi cabinet... is now putting its whole energy into the
revitalization of Japan's economy, the most important issue of the
moment," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I will convey to her our cabinet's determination to make every
possible effort for Japan's economic recovery," he added.
</P>
<P>
Komura said he would provide Albright with details about
government measures to address the country's banking problems and
cut taxes during their meeting.
</P>
<P>
He said they would also discuss the financial crisis gripping
other Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to confirm with Secretary Albright the
necessity of coordinated assistance between Japan and the United
States for the Asian economic recovery,"Komura said. 
