<HEADLINE> U.N. to Coordinate Action on Small Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan has designated the Department for Disarmament Affairs
as the focal point to coordinate all action on small arms within
the U.N. system, it was announced here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A panel set up recently by the Department includes all
departments and agencies with comparative advantages in pursuing
the objectives of the U.N. policy on small arms, the Department
said in a press statement.
</P>
<P>
Among others, the objectives are:
</P>
<P>
-- to retain its lead in putting the issue on the global
agenda;
</P>
<P>
-- to determine priorities for international action;
</P>
<P>
-- to encourage civil society involvement in building
resistance to violence, and
</P>
<P>
-- to strengthen U.N. capability for responding to requests for
assistance by affected countries.
</P>
<P>
On the panel's agenda is an international conference on illicit
arms trade to be hosted by Switzerland in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. has attached great importance to the issue of small
arms as these arms are closely related to armed conflicts in the
world today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
